        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 348 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New Lenox, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Homer Glen, Palos Park, Lemont, Lockport, Fairmont, Orland Park,
Worth, Palos Heights, Palos Hills, Romeoville, Crest Hill, New Lenox,
Bolingbrook, Joliet, Woodridge, and Mokena.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
